ithub.com/users/bantu/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bantu/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bantu/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bantu/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bantu/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bantu/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"milestone":null,"comments":4,"created_at":"2013-08-13t19:06:50z","updated_at":"2013-08-14t02:27:52z","closed_at":"2013-08-14t02:27:52z","pull_request":{"html_url":null,"diff_url":null,"patch_url":null},"body":"while trying to install owncloud 5.0.10 using mysql and nginx, i kept getting the message\r\n````\r\nmdb2 error: connect failed: _doconnect: [error message: unable to establish a connection] [native code: 0]\r\n````\r\ni confirmed at the command line that the username and password i was supplying were correct with ```mysql -u owncloud -p```. that worked fine.\r\n\r\nlooking in the ```config/config.php``` file i saw that the value for the ```dbpassword``` written there was missing the last character.  in my case, the last character was an exclamation point (!).\r\n\r\nmanually editing the config.php to supply the missing character allowed me to proceed with the installation.  i did not do any additional testing to see whether this is limited to exclamation points specifically, or punctuation generally.","closed_by":{"login":"skpy","id":722830,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/1a320ac7f6818504df79fe42fc6b84a9?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2f79f5d9584f05751f59e0b85e7f250245.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"1a320ac7f6818504df79fe42fc6b84a9","url":"https://api.github.com/users/skpy","html_url":"https://github.com/skpy","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/skpy/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/skpy/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/skpy/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/u